article.headline: Cal Poly 72, UC Davis 68
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Tyler McGinn scored a game-high 14 points, including back-to-back 3-pointers that broke a late tie and lifted Cal Poly to a 72-68 nonconference victory over UC Davis Thursday. McGinn hit 4 of 5 from beyond the arc, hitting the two 3s after the Aggies roared back from a 37-23 halftime deficit to tie it 58-58 with less than 7 minutes remaining. It was the Mustangs' first win over UC Davis since 1993. Cal Poly (7-8) shot 51.2 percent from the floor and overcame 21 turnovers. Trae Clark scored 12 points and Dawin Whiten added 11 points and five assists for the Mustangs. UC Davis (2-12) hit just 37.3 percent of its field goals and went 9 of 29 from beyond the arc against Cal Poly's zone defense. The Aggies were led by Dominic Calegari's 15 points.
